ANC MP Bongani Bongo's criminal case has been postponed. Courtesy #DStv403 NELSPRUIT - ANC MP Bongani Bongo's criminal case has been postponed. The former State Security Minister and others are facing corruption, fraud and money laundering charges. READ: Corruption case against Bongani Bongo dismissed Bongo appeared briefly in the Nelspruit Magistrate's Court in Mpumalanga on Tuesday morning. The charges relate to alleged dodgy land deals amounting to hundreds of millions of rand.